## Germplasm Phenotype:
   - [trx h9]()&nbsp;---&nbsp;Roots and leaves of  the homozygous mutants were significantly shorter and smaller  than wild-type. Root tips of 7-day-old mutant seedlings  grown on MS medium with 1% sucrose had a shortened apical  meristem and, cells were more compact, in keeping with noticeably  shorter roots. When grown in soil, mutant  plants were dwarf with small yellowish leaves.
